text: Hi there. I just wanted to say that you're the most amazing girl ever. I still don't know how I ended up with you. It's unreal. I'm so lucky. I'm honestly getting choked up just writing this. You mean the world to me, and words just can't express how much. And how much I love you. You're so dang amazing, every part of you. Your wonderful personality, your heart, your smile. You're so beautiful too. And that's just a bonus, because even though you are so insanely beautiful, I love you for you. I don't deserve you. I really don't. But I have you, and it's like a miracle. Never in the world would I ever think I could be with someone as amazing as you. I know I'm probably the worst boyfriend ever. But that doesn't stop me from trying, and from loving you. This doesn't even come close to expressing how much you mean to me. It's too much. Neither can anything express how amazing you are. When I'm missing you, I just feel empty. I hope this doesn't scare you away or anything. I need you. Remember when I promised that I will never leave you? Well I really do promise. I can't think about that. It hurts to. Sometimes I get confused, and I can't tell what you are thinking. It scares me. Sometimes I don't know what's happening, and we're up and down a lot. And it really does scare me. And I act weirdly I'm sure. I'm sorry for all of my mistakes. For everything I mess up, and for all of my imperfections. I try to do better, but some things are just hard to do, even for someone I love. Some things are just who I am. I want you to have the best, and sometimes I feel like I can't do that, That scares me so much. But I can't give you up. I never can. You're worth too much to me. You're worth anything. And I just love you. Please don't take this in the wrong way, or let it freak you out. I just want to tell you how much I love you, and how amazing you really are. I love you, my Stephanie.

text:
Prompt

Write a one page, typed response to the following quotation or statement. Do you agree or disagree with the statement? Support your position (in other words, why do you agree or disagree?). How does this statement relate to American Government? Give examples.

The best argument against democracy is a five-minute conversation with the average voter. -Winston Churchill

name: Rohan Nagar
text:
Response Essay 1
	The level of success democracy has depends on the level of education that the citizens and voters in the country have. When people go to vote for their next representative or even the president, they need to have some idea of what their policies are, how they will behave in office, and who the opponents are and what they would do instead. This way, if people know the most they can about an election, they will make the best vote on who they truly want to win.
	However, this is not how democracy is happening right now, and that is why I agree with Churchill's statement. Today, you could go down the street and ask 100 people who their house representative is, and probably at least 75 out of 100 couldn't tell you that name. Ask about Obama's policy on immigration, and maybe even less would know the answer. 
	Most people in our society are uneducated and uninformed, and that just does not work in a democracy. If people don't know who or why they are voting for someone, then there is no purpose in voting. Democracy was established so that people could have more of a say in their government. That doesn't mean just throwing your vote in there based on how a candidate looks or what feeling you have about him/her; it means that you educate yourself to the extent where you can make an informed decision on who you want your rulers to be.
	American Government is based on a democracy, with its principle that people should be engaged in the government and push for votes and laws to be made. What Churchill said is true in the American Government – people just aren't as engaged in the government as they should be. True, lots of people have opinions on candidates and laws that are made – but they need to back it up with a why. People will be quick to tell you that they dislike Obama's presidency, but when you ask them why, they don't know how to respond. Once again, their lack of education shows.

name: Rohan Nagar
text:
Response Essay 1
	The level of success democracy has depends largely on the level of education that the citizens and voters in the country have. When people go to vote for their next representative or even the president, they need to have some idea of what their policies are, how they will behave in office, and who the opponents are and what they would do instead. This way, if people know the most they can about an election, they will make the best vote on who they truly want to win.
	However, this is not how democracy is happening right now, and that is why I agree with Churchill's statement. Today, you could go down the street and ask 100 people who their house representative is, and probably at least 75 out of 100 couldn't tell you that name. Ask about Obama's policy on immigration, and maybe even less would know the answer. One way people love to vote is based on appearance. You may hear someone say, “he looks like a good guy,” or, “he looks like he knows what he's doing”. Clearly, this is the wrong mindset to have when choosing a candidate, but it happens so often in our world.
	Most people in our society are uneducated and uninformed, and that just does not work in a democracy. If people don't know who or why they are voting for someone, then there is no purpose in voting. Democracy was established so that people could have more of a say in their government. That doesn't mean just throwing your vote in there based on how a candidate looks or what feeling you have about him/her; it means that you educate yourself to the extent where you can make an informed decision on who you want your leaders to be.
	American Government is based on a democracy, with its principle that people should be engaged in the government and push for votes and laws to be made. What Churchill said is true in the American Government – people just aren't as engaged in the government as they should be. True, lots of people have opinions on candidates and laws that are made – but they need to back it up with a why. People will be quick to tell you that they dislike Obama's presidency, but when you ask them why, they don't know how to respond. Once again, their lack of education shows.
	Democracy is revolutionary. It's a form of government people want to have; it gives them a voice that is heard. However, democracy cannot work as it is intended unless people become educated in politics. Right now, anyone can argue against democracy with that idea – and they would be right.

name: Rohan Nagar
text: Hey, just thinking about you. I need to say something. My love for you, exceeds everything that I thought was possible. I never believed that a feeling could be so strong before this. I never knew. I know that my love can seem selfish at times. Heck probably more than just a few times. When you love someone so much I think there's the tendency for that to happen. But all I know is I care about you more than me. I know, it's hard to see. But really, if it was your happiness for my life, I'd make that deal. Yes, I know I try hard to keep you with me.. Yes that is selfish of me. I only do it because I'm scared. I'm scared what my life would be without you. You've brought really the only meaning I've had in my life.. If it's taken from me I don't know what would happen. I truly feel like you are a part of me and that I need you. But you come first. Always. I believe that love is two things, at least. Caring unconditionally for the other person, and needing that person in your life, just being themselves. That is what I have, and what I feel. I want to be in your life because I feel like I can help you get through anything, and you can do the same for me. You already have, helped me in so many ways. You may not even know of them all. With everything I feel, I really believe I can do anything for you. I will do anything for you. That's not something everyone can say. I wish I could show you better. And maybe I make too big a deal out of everything. I'm sorry for that. I just worry. I care about you, that's all.

name: Stephanie Tran
text: You..CAN'T be scared. Being scared doesn't get you anywhere. Holding onto something vainly does not get you anywhere; it won't help you in anyway. When you love someone, you CAN'T be selfish. Love is pain in that way, but love triggers different feelings in different people, and selfishness and/or greed should not be feelings that you let lead your actions. Because then it looks like you don't love that person. It looks like you don't want that person to be happy because you hope that they can be happy only when they're with you. You want that person to need you. You feel hurt if it's not you they are running towards. Personally, when I'm really hurt, I'd always tell you. Because you're comforting and it makes me feel better. I know you're there. But I don't know how I feel when you tell me you love me anymore. I'm starting to know that love....    is great. It's an overflowing feeling. And it's really, really painful when you're in love by yourself. And then a part of me thinks that you think you love me.. when perhaps you might just be really sensitive towards girls. I say if you don't want to hurt anymore.. and if I really loved that person .. if I want them to be happy.. let them try to find what they're looking for. And if the relationship is happy love they'll come back! Maybe they just need a break. But if they don't go back, you have to know it wasn't good for you anyways. You hurt more than you were happy. Just think that. Think about all the bad things and you'll move on faster. About my feelings, I don't know what I am feeling. I know it is towards the negative side though. But you must not let greed take over love. It doesn't make anyone happy.

name: Rohan Nagar
text: Yes I'm being selfish right now. But you can't tell me that you didn't feel the same way at one point. But I'm getting through it. I can guarantee you that my love is not selfish. You are the sole reason for my love. I love everything about you, who you are, heck down to the last strand of hair on your head. The selfishness that I encountered recently is not me. That's not who I am. And I've realized so much now. All I've ever wanted in this relationship is for two happy people. You have brought me the only happiness I have. Now I need to return that. If that means you have to leave me to me happy, then that is what has to happen. That doesn't mean I want it to, it means that if it makes you happy, that's all I care about. I WANT you to be happy. Really. You doing things for me is nice, and it's warming to me. But I don't need it. The one thing I want is your happiness and if you're happier and better off without me, then that is what you will do. I can't ask you to stay with me. But I love you. Not because I want it, but because of you. I couldn't care less about any other girl. I am not sensitive toward other girls, because they are not you. I love you. I love you, and as much as it hurts, if you have to go, then go be happy. It does hurt when you're in love by yourself. At one point you said that you were in love with me, and that was the best feeling I had ever experienced. But it sucks, when your love for that one person, and that one person only, is so great and it's so apparent to you; but they can't see it. As much pain and issues that we go through though, it's still the happiest I've ever been. That may not be true for you. But it is for me. I could never only think about the bad things.. I only want good memories. I want to remember the feelings I have. But I want you to be happy. That's what I want. And I do truly love you. It's not selfish love. That is past me now. It's about you.

name: Stephanie Tran
text: There were both small things and big things. Most importantly,  I changed my mindset.  I was very anxious before but I've learned to look at the privileges and every good thing in my life. I've rearranged my room.... minimized my clothing items, increased my awareness on food intake,  I started to read more,  go to bed earlier,  listen to people more,  stopped working,  changed my major and just stopped doing things that I "kinda" liked or didn't like at all (of course there are exceptions). I am basically changing the things that I can control in my life to change my outlook. And it's awesome. I've been noticing internal growth in the short 2 weeks (haha), and I don't know what will happen next,  but this is the most joyful I have ever been. I've also become, as a result of the changes,  a lot more sensitive. I just know that I appreciate my life so much more than I did this time last year. I mean yeah, I know why, but it’s still going to fuck with me. It's going to kill me inside that I can't be with you or hold your hand or kiss you again. Fuck am I going to miss kissing you. And how it felt every time I hugged you or every time I got a text from you. It's going kill me for a very long time. It hurts. Honestly this probably feels worse than last time because everything felt so perfect this time. You’d been the perfect partner to me. I felt like I was in heaven every time I was with you. It really hurts to let go of the best couple months I’ve had in a long time. Ah fuck. But you know, even with all that, what's hurting me the most is the thought that I won't get to hang out with you. That I won't get to make jokes or laugh with you or share the funny shit we find on the internet. Or that I won't get to even go out for a walk down by the lake and talk to you. That's what's really killing me. Forget the relationship part, you have been one of my best friends recently. I know that at the very least that I want to be your friend. Because I don't know how I can do it if I can't talk to you again. I don’t know how I did it the last time. I guess I just have more emotions now or some shit. But you’ve been such a big part of my life and without you being a part of it there’s going to be a void. I understand that you'll need some time first. I probably need some time too even though it hurts like hell. I mean damn, more time spent not talking to you? I had enough of that shit the last couple years before we started talking again. Fuck. I really really wish it would've worked and I'll probably feel that way for a long while. But all I know is that it's so much fun spending time with you. I truly enjoy talking with you and just going out and doing fun things. I feel like I can talk to you about anything. And to be honest, I need a friend like that in my life. You came back into my life for a reason, and even if we know deep down that we can't make it work in a relationship, we can still have fun together and be there for each other. So anyway, when you're ready to go grab a coffee and hang out as good friends, tell me and I'm there. I want to be able to hang out with you and joke and laugh and have deep talks and to be really good friends. I don't want this to separate us forever. Fuck. I’m really sorry again for all this, I know this probably makes it hurt more. I tried not to send this but shit I had to say something. I just felt like I couldn’t leave it the way that we did, and I think I would've exploded from everything I've been feeling. And sorry for rambling and the big ass novel I just wrote, I wasn’t planning on writing so much. Thanks for reading and thanks again for everything. I hope we talk soon.

text: today i learned about saturated, unsaturated and trans-fats, and it turns out that we should never eat anything that has trans-fat or hydrogenated oils in it because our bodies don't have the protein to break down trans-fat. But it's good to have a little bit of saturated fat in our diet (15-20g per day) and unsaturated fat is the healthiest because it has the lowest melting point temperature, so it won't clog in our system and can be used as energy faster. also, we talked about anti-inflammatory diets today that are made of unprocessed foods that won't upset your body. When your body is inflamed, the cytokine protein is released (like when you are injured, have a cut and your body knows that it needs healing). When you have too much processed food, this protein is released but has nowhere to go, or no action to take care of, and it's bad for your body if this protein is chronically being released. i found this chart and i think it's cool! it includes omega-3 fatty acids too which is essential to health because our bodies don't naturally produce it

text: "Loving someone is like moving into a house... at first you fall in love with all the new things, amazed every morning that all this belongs to you, as if fearing that someone would suddenly come rushing in through the door to explain that a terrible mistake had been made, you weren't actually supposed to live in a wonderful place like this. Then over the years the walls become weathered, the wood splinters here and there, and you start to love that house not so much because of all its perfection, but rather for its imperfections. You get to know all the nooks and crannies. How to avoid getting the key caught in the lock when it's cold outside. Which of the floorbands flex slightly when one steps on them or exactly how to open the wardrobe doors without them creaking. These are the little secrets that make it your home."

text:
I lay in my bed,
Mind racing at night.
I think of a girl,
Who is far from my side.

I think of her laugh,
And her beautiful smile.
I think of her touch,
And her wonderful mind.

I start my drift into sleep,
I wonder what she is thinking.
Or if she is asleep,
I wonder what she is dreaming.

I think of her love,
I think of our life.
Oh how lucky I am to love her,
Nothing feels more right.

Sleep begins to take hold,
And as time slows and light fades,
I swear I can feel her,
Her heart right next to mine.
